The course presents both, the cross-cultural and the historical approach, linking findings from cultural psychology to child development. Cross-cultural comparisons will be presented, including those involving Estonians participants.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the course is to provide insight into the variety of  socio-cultural contexts in which child development occurs, and to promote their culture-sensitivity and tolerance for different ways of child-rearing.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completion the student: - Knows the recent findings of cross- cultural research on child development and parenting; - Notices the cultural and contextual variety in child development - Becomes a culture-sensitive psychologist, teacher or just person;  - Adapts culture-specific intervention, teaching, child-rearing or communicative practices  - Takes the context of child development into account when planning his/her own research.
